# DeviceControl = once (no retransmit storm)

**Disc:** `docs/MOB-DISC-DEVICE-CONTROL-PREVENTION-WHO-AND-HOW-20260723.md`  
**PASS fix:** `DEVICE-CONTROL-SIP-NO-RETRANSMIT-STORM-V1`  
**Prevention:** `docs/MOB-DISC-DEVICE-CONTROL-NEVER-RETRANSMIT-STORM-PREVENTION-20260723.md`

## Locked (operator PASS 2026-07-23)

1 click Snapshot / Record / Lock / … → **1** SIP MESSAGE on the wire → **1** BWC effect.

## Agent MUST

- Keep DeviceControl default **`udp_once`** in `lib/deviceControl.js`
- Route one-shot cam commands through **`deviceControl.sendDeviceControl`** only
- After any DeviceControl MOB: prove log `mode:"udp_once"` + operator one physical effect

## Agent MUST NOT

- Switch DeviceControl back to `sip.send` / `mode:"sip_txn"` “for reliability” without **`MOB-APPLY`** naming that change
- Set or recommend **`FM_DEVICE_CONTROL_SIP_TXN=1`** for normal lab or customer ship
- Add a second TakePicture / Record / Lock path via raw `sip.send({ method: 'MESSAGE' …})` outside `deviceControl.js`
- Blame “debounce the button” when log already shows 1× `device control sent` with txn/408 history

## Not the same bug

PTT group XML / status / INVITE may still use `sip.send` — those are not shutter one-shots. Do not “udp_once everything” without a named MOB.

## If multi-fire returns

1. Count `device control sent` and read **`mode`**
2. `sip_txn` → regression / hatch — stop and fix  
3. `udp_once` + still many → device burst/firmware — not Timer E
